<item>
            <title>[SOLR-3108] Error in SolrCloud&apos;s replica lookup code when replica&apos;s are hosted in same Solr instance</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3108</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a small bug in ZkStateReader.getReplicaProps() when you have multiple replicas of the same shard/slice hosted in one CoreContainer. Not that you would often do this, but I was playing around with shards &amp;amp; replicas using just one Solr instance and noticed it. The attached patch should make it clear, the check on !coreNodeName.equals(filterNodeName) will always be false in such case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Solr trunk as of today (r1241575)&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
